description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Royal Brompton and Harefield NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harefield Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locum Consultant Haematologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reference: 312-HH-&lt;strong&gt;LCON-LAB-0011&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal Brompton &amp; Harefield NHS Foundation Trust is renowned nationally and internationally for excellence in diagnosis, treatment and research of patients with cardiothoracic diseases. It is the largest postgraduate specialist heart and lung centre in the United Kingdom with sites in Chelsea, London and Harefield, Middlesex. We strive to develop our staff both personally and professionally to ensure our patients get the first-class service they deserve.Harefield Hospital is also one of UK’s largest heart and lung transplant centres.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic part-time or full-time locum consultant haematologist based mainly at Harefield Hospital, although the successful applicant may be required to work in other locations in the Trust. This post is for 12 months in the first instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder along with other Consultant haematologists will be responsible for delivering the Trust’s haematology service comprising support and leadership for the haematology laboratory&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide appropriate advice on the most suitable methods for diagnosis, timing of investigations and interpretation of laboratory results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will participate in and contribute to the proper functioning and efficient running of the Laboratory Medicine Directorate and participate in audit. It is expected that the appointee will show a commitment to continuing medical education (CME) and be expected to participate in CPD and in relevant quality assurance schemes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries may be made to Professor Michael Loebinger,Clinical Director of Laboratory Medicine, (email: m.loebinger@rbht.nhs.uk) or Penny Agent,Director of Allied Clinical Sciences, (email: p.agent@rbht.nhs.uk) Alternatively you can contact Sophia White, Medical Recruitment team on 020 7351 8688 or email s.white3@rbht.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please apply for the position using the &quot;Apply for this job&quot; button. Please complete the online application form and include the full names, work addresses and fax numbers of three clinical referees, one of which must be your current or most recent employer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shortlisting details and interview arrangements will be communicated via email therefore please ensure you check your email account regularly following the closing date. In addition the Trust will be chasing up references via email so please ensure you include the email addresses and contact numbers for your referees to avoid delay in the recruitment process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: Thursday 12th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: TBC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
